<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1932-10-28T08:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1932-10-28T08:00:00-05:00" n="580" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d580">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">393.1111 <persName corresp="frus1932v03#p_NBN1">Nelson, Bert N.</persName>/149:
                            Telegram</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The Minister in China (<persName corresp="frus1932v03#p_JNT1" type="from">Johnson</persName>) to
                                the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss></hi></head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Peiping</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1932-10-28T21:00:00+08:00">October 28, 1932—9
                                p.m.</date><lb/>[Received October 28—2:35 a.m.]</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>1219. Legation’s 1118, September 21, 1 p.m. In despatch October 14th
                            American Consul General at Hankow reports that a Chinese messenger sent
                            by <persName corresp="frus1932v03#p_JNT1">Nelson</persName>’s friends
                            stated that he found <persName corresp="frus1932v03#p_JNT1">Nelson</persName> on a high mountain about 36 miles from Chiliping,
                            Hupeh, and that <persName corresp="frus1932v03#p_JNT1">Nelson</persName>
                            appeared to be in good health.</p>
                        <p>2. In telegram October 26 <persName corresp="frus1932v03#p_AWA1">Adams</persName> reports that he had received a telegram from
                                <persName corresp="frus1932v03#p_SCC1">Skinsnes</persName> at
                            Sinyangchow to the effect that report of the Chinese messenger was false
                            and that <persName corresp="frus1932v03#p_JNT1">Nelson</persName> was
                            probably killed by Reds August 21st. <persName corresp="frus1932v03#p_AWA1">Adams</persName> is telegraphing for
                            detailed information.</p>
                        <closer><signed><persName corresp="frus1932v03#p_JNT1"><hi rend="smallcaps">Johnson</hi></persName></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>